# li-tests

All conformance tests live in `li-tests/`. Do not add scattered fixtures under `compiler/`.

## Register every test

1. Add `.li` under the correct suite directory  
2. Add `[[tests]]` entry to `li-tests/manifest.toml` with `outcome`  
3. For `compile_fail`, set `expected_substr` or add `file.exp`  

## Outcomes

| outcome | Meaning |
|---------|---------|
| `parse_ok` / `parse_fail` | Parser stage |
| `compile_ok` / `compile_fail` | Type + borrow (no Lean yet) |
| `verify_ok` / `verify_fail` | Full `lic build` + Lean |

## Suites

`race_shared_memory` — exploit tests; failures must cite shared memory / disjoint / Sync.

Run: `./li-tests/run_all.sh` or `./li-tests/run_all.sh <suite>`
